  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled $25,000 and has already begun making restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the relative scale of the theft and the absence of a criminal record mitigate a long prison sentence. The outburst by the spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case and was disregarded. Taking into account the need for punishment and rehabilitation, I find that a sentence served in a county facility is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
